content.description: second route from the left, next to The Lost Bolt.  Starts in the Slanting route starts left and climbs right. finishes same as One eye Rosie.
content.protection: trad route. anchors on the top but you can walk off.

content.description: Climb a greasy smooth face left of a large roof--the crux. The upper section is gently overhanging and a little runout, but with plenty of good holds. --"Northern Utah: Limestone Climbing"
content.protection: Bolts to Chains. The route is just left of Alyosha.

content.description: Starts left of Jollymon and climbs hidden clips to the first set of anchors.  The 2nd pitch goes at 5.7 and can be linked with a longer rope.
content.protection:
5 bolts for the 5.11a

10 bolts if you link them.
content.location: Left of Jollymon and starts on two obvious crimps.

content.description: Great 5.7, one of the best in the canyon.  Has a few moves that make people use their feet.  Great first lead.
content.location: Farthest route up the wall, follows a line of bolts to the chains at the top, rap down, or climb to the top and walk off to the North.

content.description: This is a great route with thoughtful movement. The holds are sometimes a little tricky to find, but they are all there.
content.location: This is the first route that you come to as you arrive at the wall from the trail. Facing the wall, it is the farthest to the right.

content.description: Fun climbing up to a technical crux towards the top.  You can keep going past the first set of chains, but the climbing gets considerably easier (5.4 range) and the bolts are fairly sketchy.
content.protection: Bolts and chains, bring some webbing just incase the top (second pitch) chains are sketchy.
content.location: Third bolted route from the left (top), starts in a polished crack and follows the bolts up to a chain anchor, there are more bolts to another set of chains up top, but it's rarely done.  Possible to walk off to the North if you continue up over the top.

content.description: Climb up the face, pull a roof with a heinous finger lock and continue up a gently overhanging face.
content.protection: A stopper is advised for those not wishing to run out the upper section. Easily toproped.
content.location: When facing the wall, the furthest climb to the right.
